overview: The user initiated a request to fix all outstanding issues in a pull
  request, emphasizing critical Vercel deployment failures. The agent
  systematically addressed a wide array of problems, starting with lint errors
  and progressing to significant security vulnerabilities like trivially
  forgeable admin cookies, which were resolved by implementing a robust
  HMAC-based session management system. Input validation was enhanced for API
  routes, and CSV export was optimized to prevent memory exhaustion. Numerous
  bugs related to PDF generation, form field behavior, and UI functionality were
  also fixed. A substantial portion of the effort was dedicated to
  troubleshooting persistent Vercel deployment issues. This involved refactoring
  the authentication logic to be compatible with Vercel's Edge Runtime,
  correcting a missing database URL in the Prisma schema, and updating Next.js
  to patch a critical security vulnerability. Ultimately, the Vercel deployments
  were still failing due to unconfigured environment variables on the Vercel
  platform, which the user was advised to set manually.
